{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.8",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 8,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 8",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 8 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:1",
      "text": "Then Bildad the Shuhite answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:2",
      "text": "“How long will you say these things, and the words of your mouth be a great wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:3",
      "text": "Does God pervert justice? Or does the Almighty pervert the right?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:4",
      "text": "If your children have sinned against him, he has delivered them into the power of their transgression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:5",
      "text": "If you will seek God and make supplication to the Almighty,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:6",
      "text": "if you are pure and upright, surely then he will rouse himself for you and reward you with a rightful habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:7",
      "text": "And though your beginning was small, your latter days will be very great.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:8",
      "text": "“For inquire, I pray you, of bygone ages, and consider what the fathers have found;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:9",
      "text": "for we are but of yesterday, and know nothing, for our days on earth are a shadow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:10",
      "text": "Will they not teach you, and tell you, and utter words out of their understanding?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:11",
      "text": "“Can papyrus grow where there is no marsh? Can reeds flourish where there is no water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:12",
      "text": "While yet in flower and not cut down, they wither before any other plant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:13",
      "text": "Such are the paths of all who forget God; the hope of the godless man shall perish.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:14",
      "text": "His confidence breaks in sunder, and his trust is a spider's web.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:15",
      "text": "He leans against his house, but it does not stand; he lays hold of it, but it does not endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:16",
      "text": "He thrives before the sun, and his shoots spread over his garden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:17",
      "text": "His roots twine about the stoneheap; he lives among the rocks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:18",
      "text": "If he is destroyed from his place, then it will deny him, saying, ‘I have never seen you.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:19",
      "text": "Behold, this is the joy of his way; and out of the earth others will spring.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:20",
      "text": "“Behold, God will not reject a blameless man, nor take the hand of evildoers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:21",
      "text": "He will yet fill your mouth with laughter, and your lips with shouting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.8.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:22",
      "text": "Those who hate you will be clothed with shame, and the tent of the wicked will be no more.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
